ttps://example-market.com/pages — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Extract Listings (CSS) · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"f67c4186-b883-3a12-a440-b02ca7643b45","name":"Note: Fetch Target Page"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Extract Listings (CSS)\n\nExtracts structured values from raw HTML via CSS selectors.\n\nNext: Rows from Arrays","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"c0b007ce-19fe-ef57-c2d0-9df377d900ff","name":"Note: Extract Listings (CSS)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Rows from Arrays\n\nCustom JavaScript: Zip parallel arrays into one item per listing\n\nNext: Diff vs Last Run","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"5c09b28e-ef47-1513-39a1-84d8f87d5a06","name":"Note: Rows from Arrays"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nSearches Airtable's 'Pages' table by formula (`={LastModified} > DATEADD(NOW(), -1, 'days')`) for records the pipeline hasn't handled yet.\n\nPorts: ①→ Diff vs Last Run · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,1030],"id":"b5549365-bcef-ad1d-8cb9-5814a0a75bf0","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Diff vs Last Run\n\nDiffs two streams by key into 4 lanes: only-in-A, same, different, only-in-B — the heart of the sync.\n\nPorts: ①→ Alert New Findings · ③→ Update Changed Rows · ④→ Write Fresh Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,520],"id":"69179dc3-810f-f539-d46c-7170d8ebdb7a","name":"Note: Diff vs Last Run"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Alert New Findings\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Diff Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,40],"id":"e463380c-d823-1c4e-4b82-8299108558f0","name":"Note: Alert New Findings"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Update Changed Rows\n\nUpserts into Airtable's 'Pages' table, matched on `pageId` — safe to re-run without creating duplicates.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Diff Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,580],"id":"e33e3ba6-6b96-bfe4-3bfd-fab08cb0a79f","name":"Note: Update Changed Rows"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Write Fresh Snapshot\n\nCreates a new record in Airtable's 'Pages' table.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Diff Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,1090],"id":"750fc63e-59fe-3db2-959b-038a08546c0b","name":"Note: Write Fresh Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Diff Outcomes\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"a532f2af-e9c5-bba9-482b-5f4845b12e9f","name":"Note: Merge Diff Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"bdf921d1-e710-f3cb-4951-e5598bc661f6","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"2443444c-1841-8db7-16d7-041fb36d2e5c","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"968886ab-327c-e9f2-1aef-ded4d6413820","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"5fb75dec-0ea3-354e-552d-011287fdd7d2","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per page (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"e31f3aa2-645d-8721-c2e7-da11b6b5d8a5","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot 2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"72251499-1c80-84c3-7360-08ce4440b16b","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot 2\n\nPulls every page from the Notion database — fine for small datasets; add a filter if the database grows large.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"4573d125-5210-2d82-0ca5-c27dbc24821c","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot 2"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"088005f7-0894-ffe9-39d6-d4c7bce57a5c","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"ac1ea518-db37-8e0c-fa98-7fb8973a8c3c","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nAppends a new row to 'Page Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Enrich with Reference Data · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"f0d75a9f-773a-65df-be5b-dd0e66c8eb0c","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"849dc013-7203-c780-6be7-134f4ee56bc0","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"41e86b51-c825-a3bd-cc45-b799dfdf6488","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"07da8146-245a-5375-6dc2-2afe8bcf4267","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"eb199ea0-4155-4452-5cf3-473effad9693","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 100 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"7dc2fc0b-e724-f3a1-837d-8b3cce7614d6","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"4d0bdac1-c815-e7c8-b840-4a7dd0d2629e","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"56a136bd-b5be-ef91-34b0-4c7d6fd0b64d","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10362,520],"id":"47ee0e70-6299-54a4-4a46-4a6b1109d8ae","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Outlook · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10686,520],"id":"005e7242-bd58-bc16-47e2-ad54e9aa12d2","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Outlook\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[11010,520],"id":"a3f03dbd-3b6d-e760-ff9d-e3d20415a5ff","name":"Note: Send Summary to Outlook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Outlook","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10362,1540],"id":"7f8514c2-43c2-064f-b560-49e39ddb5630","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Outlook\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10686,1540],"id":"80121aed-f38c-fdf9-88e8-685637a3c9ab","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Outlook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nCreates a new record in Airtable's 'Pages' table.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[11010,1540],"id":"aaec06da-0e40-94b8-fa42-ba0df8d67032","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Report on site health with HTTP / REST API and Airtable in real time\n\n**Pattern:** SEO Audit · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nReport on site health with HTTP / REST API and Airtable in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual content seo is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Fetch Target Page → Extract Listings (CSS) → Rows from Arrays → Diff vs Last Run → Alert New Findings → Merge Diff Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to seo audit without manual effort\n- Anyone automating content seo in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Improves response time\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Airtable PAT; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"591bae1b-2cdf-a5b3-661f-9eeb2e7816f0","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nEvery run diffs against the previous snapshot instead of re-alerting on everything scraped — without this, the workflow would spam the same unchanged listings on every scheduled run. The three-way split (new / changed / unchanged) means each gets exactly the treatment it needs: alert, update, or a silent snapshot refresh.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"a20d0114-6ea1-1773-fea7-36807eeab970","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Change the CSS selectors to scrape a different site's listing structure.\n2. Manually edit one row in the snapshot store and confirm it's flagged as changed on the next run.\n3. Add a price-drop-specific alert condition on top of the generic new/changed diff.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"938a62ad-fd01-0b25-03fa-047edb999437","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"1e472648-d357-43ee-daf4-a74d35cdec81","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"6649c739-2cd4-943d-903a-f6d561d24e47","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your content seo process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"cfc06137-543f-7350-43b1-dd0c5dbfee2b","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Daily Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Fetch Target Page","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fetch Target Page":{"main":[[{"node":"Extract Listings (CSS)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Extract Listings (CSS)":{"main":[[{"node":"Rows from Arrays","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Rows from Arrays":{"main":[[{"node":"Diff vs Last Run","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Diff vs Last Run","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Diff vs Last Run":{"main":[[{"node":"Alert New Findings","type":"main","index":0}],[],[{"node":"Update Changed Rows","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Write Fresh Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Alert New Findings":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Diff Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Update Changed Rows":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Diff Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Write Fresh Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Diff Outcomes","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Diff Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot 2","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot 2":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Outlook","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Outlook","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Outlook":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Outlook":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"Daily Schedule":[{"json":{"pageId":"PG-201","url":"/blog/n8n-workflow-examples","keyword":"n8n workflow examples","position":6}},{"json":{"pageId":"PG-202","url":"/blog/n8n-vs-zapier","keyword":"n8n vs zapier","position":11}}]},"versionId":"526dcec5-82ce-472f-8670-ca3e77da1190","id":"FDX10160"}